      "title": "Parallel Reading",
      "subtitle": "Read several sources at once to expose shared claims, tensions, and gaps.",
      "tags": ["throughput"],
      "pairedWithIds": [],
      "body": "Reading multiple books at once allows you to unlock many benifits that you would not get from reading one book at a time. You'll learn to discursively read, to make reading sessions more consistent, and to drop books caught in sunk cost fallacies.",
